WEBVTT

00:01.080 --> 00:04.720
MICHAEL: <i>Until further notice,
no fraternising with the foreigners.</i>

00:04.800 --> 00:08.200
My son will walk
with any woman in this city.

00:08.320 --> 00:10.400
JOHN: It would be hard for your son
to walk anywhere

00:10.480 --> 00:12.000
with a bullet in each knee.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.160
You said you wanted peace at home.

00:15.240 --> 00:16.560
Now, we go on the offensive.

00:18.720 --> 00:20.520
RUBEN: <i>A woman of substance and class.</i>

00:20.600 --> 00:21.640
And I've painted many women.

00:21.720 --> 00:22.920
There'll be no charge.

00:23.400 --> 00:25.760
TOMMY: The name I've heard is Section D.

00:25.840 --> 00:28.480
MPs, army officers...

00:28.560 --> 00:30.840
When all we're trying to do
is save the country from revolution.

00:31.000 --> 00:35.160
This is for the killing of the spy
and a down payment on future services.

00:35.600 --> 00:37.880
TATIANA: Does your wife know
that the sapphire she is wearing

00:37.960 --> 00:39.000
has been cursed?

00:39.080 --> 00:41.480
Nothing on Earth would make me wear it.

00:41.560 --> 00:43.400
For Angel!

00:54.000 --> 00:56.000
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

02:11.640 --> 02:12.920
ADA: He's back.

02:14.320 --> 02:15.960
MICHAEL: Was he out there all night?

02:16.640 --> 02:18.320
Every night since the funeral.

02:18.840 --> 02:21.520
Comes back in the morning to see Charles
and feed the horses,

02:21.600 --> 02:23.840
and when it gets dark,
he goes off again.

02:25.520 --> 02:27.360
He used to sleep out when he was a kid.

02:28.840 --> 02:30.720
Curly would find him in the pasture.

02:32.800 --> 02:34.240
How's the baby?

02:35.600 --> 02:37.400
ADA: He asks for him mum at night.

02:38.560 --> 02:41.120
(CLICKS TONGUE) Tommy made a list.

02:41.200 --> 02:42.840
He wants to see you two first.

02:42.920 --> 02:45.200
-What about John and Arthur?
-(DOOR OPENS)

02:55.200 --> 02:56.200
(DOOR CLOSES)

03:05.320 --> 03:06.480
How are the books?

03:10.280 --> 03:11.280
Unaffected.

03:12.120 --> 03:13.640
Up slightly.

03:16.520 --> 03:18.800
There's also been a threefold increase
in donations

03:18.880 --> 03:20.760
to the Shelby Foundation charity.

03:22.160 --> 03:26.240
The counsellor suggested naming the
new school "The Grace Shelby Institute."

03:33.040 --> 03:36.480
Tell the counsellor the name "Grace
Shelby Institute" is acceptable to us.

03:36.560 --> 03:37.560
(SNIFFS)

03:42.600 --> 03:44.960
This is a list on the other things
I want doing.

03:46.480 --> 03:47.640
That's all.

03:49.320 --> 03:50.600
(CLEARS THROAT)

03:55.640 --> 03:57.080
-Tommy.
-That's all, Pol.

04:07.640 --> 04:09.200
Well done, both of you.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.680
Right, let's go.

04:20.760 --> 04:21.960
Uh, we've already seen him.

04:27.040 --> 04:29.440
He wanted to see people
in a particular order.

04:31.920 --> 04:36.440
I can normally read him, but he's
difficult to read, so be careful.

04:37.960 --> 04:40.240
I thought it was
a fucking family meeting.

04:40.480 --> 04:42.080
All of us together, I thought.

04:42.160 --> 04:43.480
John, he's grieving.

04:43.560 --> 04:45.760
To see everyone together
would be too much.

04:46.080 --> 04:49.600
Yeah, well... Come on, John.

04:51.240 --> 04:53.040
Arthur, we need him back.

04:54.000 --> 04:58.200
Sabini and Solomons have already sent
condolences and flowers,

04:58.280 --> 05:01.320
so it won't be long before they come
trotting up the A1 like wolves.

05:01.400 --> 05:03.040
Go on. There's a timetable.

05:06.760 --> 05:08.080
POLLY: Only good news.

05:08.480 --> 05:10.200
There is only good news, Polly.

05:12.440 --> 05:13.480
Who we fucking now?

05:14.440 --> 05:17.280
Well, there he is.

05:19.720 --> 05:20.720
Hi, Tom.

05:21.160 --> 05:22.280
Hello, boys.

05:22.720 --> 05:27.840
We, uh, didn't get a chance to see you
after the funeral.

05:28.600 --> 05:32.960
Well, you disappeared on us, but, well,
me and John, we just wanna say that...

05:33.040 --> 05:34.080
Arthur, shut up.

05:34.160 --> 05:35.280
All right.

05:36.520 --> 05:38.040
All right, talk to me.

05:39.000 --> 05:43.080
We got to Angel at the hospital
where he laid. Cut his throat.

05:44.280 --> 05:45.280
He's dead.

05:46.120 --> 05:49.440
Cleared out the rest of the Italians
out of the south of the city.

05:49.520 --> 05:50.920
JOHN: They mostly went to
the Black Country,

05:51.000 --> 05:52.880
but we told Betty Kitchins
to keep her moving.

05:52.960 --> 05:54.400
And Betty sends her condolences.

05:54.480 --> 05:55.840
What about the old man?

05:56.720 --> 05:58.080
We interrogated his boys.

05:58.160 --> 05:59.680
Yeah, he went to Liverpool.

05:59.760 --> 06:01.480
He's waiting
for an immigrant ship to New York.

06:01.560 --> 06:02.920
When?

06:03.000 --> 06:04.640
Berthed ship sails Saturday.

06:05.760 --> 06:10.680
All right, I have contacts,
people in Cunard and Liverpool.

06:11.480 --> 06:12.520
They'll have passenger lists.

06:12.600 --> 06:14.720
They can get you into the point
of departure.

06:14.800 --> 06:16.480
You pick him up,
and you bring him to me.

06:16.600 --> 06:17.920
Who's he got travelling with him?

06:19.520 --> 06:21.320
-His wife.
-What?

06:22.280 --> 06:23.520
His wife.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.360
So shoot her, and bring him to me.

06:30.880 --> 06:34.800
Uh, Tommy, Mrs Changretta
was a teacher at our school.

06:34.880 --> 06:37.600
She's a good woman, Tom, a good woman.

06:42.640 --> 06:45.600
Well, if she's a good woman,
then she'll go to heaven, eh, Arthur?

06:48.200 --> 06:51.360
(EXHALES) Just do what's on the list,
nothing else. Then burn it.

06:51.440 --> 06:54.920
Don't speak on the phones.
The fucking Secret Service is listening.

06:56.120 --> 06:57.120
(SIGHS)

06:58.240 --> 07:01.000
I want the old man alive.
I wanna do it myself.

07:09.280 --> 07:10.920
That's it. (CLEARS THROAT) You can go.

07:15.720 --> 07:17.160
Come, John.

07:17.240 --> 07:21.920
Tommy, if you haven't got a bird here,
you're gonna have to tell us something.

07:22.120 --> 07:23.520
Ask Polly.

07:25.320 --> 07:26.600
Not Michael?

07:27.080 --> 07:28.080
What?

07:28.400 --> 07:29.840
-Not Michael, no?
-No.

07:29.920 --> 07:32.880
Not Michael, no. 'Cause
Michael deals with legitimate business.

07:34.000 --> 07:35.200
You saw him before us.

07:35.280 --> 07:37.640
John, not now.

07:38.080 --> 07:39.240
Wait, what did you say?

07:40.360 --> 07:42.520
You saw Michael before us!

07:42.600 --> 07:43.840
Fuck's sake, John.

07:46.400 --> 07:49.440
Because legitimate business, John,
is the priority.

07:51.440 --> 07:53.720
-Legitimate business...
-Since when?

07:53.800 --> 07:58.560
Since my fucking wife took a bullet
meant for me.

08:03.200 --> 08:05.760
(SNIFFS) Oh, yeah. OK.

08:05.840 --> 08:08.480
Yeah, so Secret Service.
Secret fucking Service...

08:08.560 --> 08:11.200
Blah, blah, blah.
But you don't tell us shit.

08:11.280 --> 08:13.920
We're a couple of fucking toy soldiers.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.760
"Do this, John. Do that, John.
Kill your fucking teacher, John!"

08:27.600 --> 08:28.920
This is how it's gonna be.

08:31.440 --> 08:34.760
All right, listen to me.
There's gonna be a little war

08:34.840 --> 08:37.960
in a little place
that no one gives a fuck about.

08:38.480 --> 08:41.560
And the side that is gonna lose
needs a little bit of help.

08:41.760 --> 08:43.440
And they're willing to pay.

08:43.520 --> 08:48.840
When that business is done,
legitimate business is the priority.

08:48.920 --> 08:52.200
Now, do what's on the list and fuck off.

08:55.080 --> 08:56.080
(SNIFFS)

09:00.880 --> 09:01.880
(EXHALES)

09:06.360 --> 09:08.360
When are you coming back, hmm?

09:09.200 --> 09:10.400
I'm back, Arthur.

09:22.360 --> 09:24.360
ARTHUR: John, you're just as young.
JOHN: Cheers.

09:24.440 --> 09:27.640
The thing is, we all naturally came
in here, where the servants eat.

09:27.720 --> 09:30.120
It's nothing to do
with politics, Ada.

09:30.200 --> 09:32.000
It's fucking freezing in the big room.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.120
John, mind your language
in front of Carl.

09:34.200 --> 09:35.960
Ada, we're in the servants' quarters

09:36.040 --> 09:38.880
because it's where the fucking booze
is kept.

09:38.960 --> 09:41.120
-Arthur, find better words!
-Yes.

09:41.200 --> 09:43.000
Pol, does swearing in Gypsy count?

09:43.080 --> 09:46.440
That's no reason for us to be speaking
Shelta in any case.

09:46.520 --> 09:48.200
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

09:48.280 --> 09:50.320
I'm just saying there is no need.

09:50.840 --> 09:53.400
When she's drunk,
my wife can't speak fucking English.

09:53.480 --> 09:54.920
-John!
-Fucking right!

09:58.800 --> 10:00.120
POLLY: You dealt with it?

10:00.200 --> 10:02.400
Incentives, no threats.

10:02.480 --> 10:05.960
Implied consequences without
specific reference to physical harm.

10:06.480 --> 10:09.400
That's why young Michael is the boss.

10:10.080 --> 10:12.760
He knows better words, right, Pol?

10:12.840 --> 10:14.480
Since when was I your boss, Arthur?

10:14.560 --> 10:17.880
First, the boss meets you.
Then the workers meet you.

10:17.960 --> 10:20.200
When did either of you two
do a day's work?

10:20.280 --> 10:21.840
ARTHUR: In the old days, Finn,

10:22.720 --> 10:26.480
family meetings
used to be all of us together.

10:26.560 --> 10:28.000
POLLY: Arthur, shut up.

10:32.640 --> 10:34.080
Now, me and John,

10:36.080 --> 10:42.240
we're just fucking bin men
whose duty it is to obey.

10:43.680 --> 10:44.680
Hmm?

10:48.920 --> 10:50.320
Mrs Changretta.

10:53.720 --> 11:00.280
Arthur, shut up.
Finn, go and get us cigars.

11:00.400 --> 11:04.200
JOHN: So what are we gonna do
all night, eh? Climb fucking trees?

11:04.280 --> 11:05.920
John, stop swearing
in front of the kids.

11:06.000 --> 11:07.640
Yeah, and who said
you're staying the night?

11:07.720 --> 11:09.120
ARTHUR: I know what we can do.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.560
We get the guns out, John.

11:12.240 --> 11:15.560
We go outside,
and we shoot some fucking pheasants.

11:16.040 --> 11:17.120
(BOTH LAUGH)

11:17.720 --> 11:19.600
-That's what the bosses do, isn't it?
-Yeah.

11:19.680 --> 11:20.880
Fuck off, Arthur.

11:23.440 --> 11:24.960
Fuck you just say to me?

11:27.000 --> 11:29.400
I didn't ask for separate meetings
today, all right?

11:29.800 --> 11:34.120
No. No, what the fuck did you just say?

11:34.480 --> 11:36.960
'Cause I didn't fucking hear you right.

11:38.320 --> 11:43.040
I didn't ask for separate meetings
today, all right?

11:43.480 --> 11:44.560
Fucking pheasant.

11:45.240 --> 11:46.520
-Carl!
-(LAUGHS)

11:46.960 --> 11:48.520
You can't say things like that.

11:48.600 --> 11:50.760
Now look what you've done.

11:53.160 --> 11:54.600
All right, brothers.

11:55.800 --> 11:57.400
It's just the fucking whisky talking.

11:57.480 --> 11:59.400
I don't ask to be protected, all right?

11:59.480 --> 12:03.040
POLLY: Right. Shut up.
The pair of you, sit down!

12:05.040 --> 12:06.360
Sit down!

12:06.640 --> 12:08.520
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-Look around you.

12:09.680 --> 12:11.080
And look at this house.

12:12.400 --> 12:13.960
Look where we are.

12:14.040 --> 12:16.320
Look how far we've come.

12:16.400 --> 12:18.480
I think it's about time
we all started acting

12:18.560 --> 12:20.760
in a way more appropriate
to our station.

12:23.120 --> 12:25.240
We're none of us bin men any more,
Arthur.

12:26.960 --> 12:28.520
Tommy needs us all together.

12:30.320 --> 12:32.120
I'd like to propose a toast.

12:34.680 --> 12:35.680
(CLEARS THROAT)

12:40.560 --> 12:44.120
It's a family united
that shall never be defeated.

12:44.360 --> 12:46.200
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

12:46.560 --> 12:49.960
Tommy's gone. Swear to God,
he's in a wagon with Johnny Dogs.

12:52.760 --> 12:53.760
Shit.

12:54.160 --> 12:55.680
This is what he does now.

13:03.880 --> 13:07.160
ARTHUR: Tommy! Wait!
POLLY: Arthur!

13:07.240 --> 13:08.880
ARTHUR: Tommy!
POLLY: Arthur, let him go!

13:09.160 --> 13:12.520
ARTHUR: Tommy! Tommy!
JOHN: Tommy! Tommy!

13:14.360 --> 13:15.600
Tommy!

13:18.440 --> 13:19.720
Walk on. Walk on.

13:21.840 --> 13:23.400
JOHNNY: Tommy.
TOMMY: Walk on.

13:24.160 --> 13:25.760
They're coming out in the drive.

13:26.360 --> 13:28.240
-You're not gonna tell them?
-Tell them what?

13:29.040 --> 13:30.440
That we're going to Wales.

13:31.040 --> 13:32.040
I left a note.

13:34.560 --> 13:35.840
Did you tell them
why we're going to Wales?

13:35.920 --> 13:36.960
No.

13:37.040 --> 13:39.160
At some point you're gonna tell me
why we're going to Wales?

13:39.240 --> 13:40.640
Yeah, when we get there.

13:41.440 --> 13:42.480
TOMMY: Walk on.

13:42.560 --> 13:44.360
Should have brought
at least one woman, Tommy.

13:44.440 --> 13:46.520
Johnny, it's a woman we're going to see.

13:47.280 --> 13:49.920
-There, boy. Walk on. Walk on.
-Right.

13:54.080 --> 13:56.680
Says he'll be back in Birmingham
in three days.

13:58.120 --> 13:59.400
POLLY: (SIGHS) Let him go.

14:00.120 --> 14:03.240
The important thing is,
if he says he'll be back, he'll be back.

14:03.960 --> 14:07.040
Come on.
Let's go light a fire in the big room.

14:07.560 --> 14:11.120
Let's go drink whisky, with water.

14:21.960 --> 14:23.400
See to the horses, Johnny.

14:23.720 --> 14:25.040
Aye, Tom.

14:31.640 --> 14:32.680
(SIGHS)

14:40.280 --> 14:44.200
So we'll go out through Meridian,
then into the Black Mountains.

14:46.800 --> 14:48.440
-Here.
-(YELLS)

14:48.520 --> 14:49.920
Here, give me some.

14:50.840 --> 14:51.880
Boy.

14:54.200 --> 14:55.280
Here you go.

14:59.560 --> 15:02.960
Now, remember last night
when you asked after Mama?

15:05.200 --> 15:08.080
She's gone, Charlie, and there's
a few things we need to get straight.

15:09.960 --> 15:11.320
There's her photographs.

15:12.400 --> 15:13.880
There's her clothes.

15:17.040 --> 15:18.960
I'll keep things the way they are
in the room. (CLEARS THROAT)

15:21.880 --> 15:25.800
Just keep things the way they are.

15:31.240 --> 15:32.280
Here you go.

15:34.320 --> 15:36.440
Yeah. Here you go.

15:38.360 --> 15:39.840
I'm not much good, Charlie.

15:41.120 --> 15:43.440
-(CHARLIE EXCLAIMS)
-You'll find that out soon enough.

15:46.760 --> 15:49.120
She's not gonna be coming back,
so it's just you and me.

15:52.440 --> 15:56.560
She'll be with us in our hearts
'cause we love her.

15:57.160 --> 15:58.200
-JOHNNY: Tommy.
-Yeah.

15:58.280 --> 16:00.080
This fucking horse of yours
won't come to me.

16:00.160 --> 16:02.080
-All right, I'll be there. All right.
-Huh? Come on.

16:04.120 --> 16:05.920
That was her favourite horse, Charlie,

16:07.640 --> 16:09.680
and he's been all over the place
since she's gone.

16:11.760 --> 16:13.320
-Tom?
-Yeah, you watch him.

16:13.400 --> 16:14.600
I will. Oh, yeah.

16:15.480 --> 16:16.480
Huh?

16:27.320 --> 16:30.480
All right, now cock it with your thumb.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.560
-(CHUCKLES)
-(GUN COCKS)

16:37.960 --> 16:41.080
There you go. Now she's been cocked.

16:41.440 --> 16:43.320
-She's alive in your hand.
-(CROWING)

16:43.800 --> 16:46.320
It's like waking up a girl
when you cock that trigger.

16:47.080 --> 16:50.400
She rolls over all sleepy-eyed
and she goes,

16:51.080 --> 16:54.640
-"Michael. Michael."
-(JOHN CHUCKLING)

16:55.760 --> 16:57.840
"What are you gonna make me do,
Michael?"

16:57.920 --> 17:01.680
You boys are fucking crazy men.

17:01.760 --> 17:04.720
-Yeah, but you feel it, though, right?
-Yeah.

17:05.120 --> 17:06.320
You feel it.

17:06.400 --> 17:08.760
Yeah, you can feel the power.

17:09.280 --> 17:12.280
Now, squeeze it.

17:15.120 --> 17:16.120
(GUNSHOT)

17:17.800 --> 17:18.960
Powerful.

17:19.040 --> 17:22.400
-Fucking useless.
-Piss off, John.

17:22.480 --> 17:29.120
Michael, why does a pen pusher who sits
on his arse all day wanna fire a gun?

17:29.400 --> 17:31.520
Hmm? Eh?

17:32.520 --> 17:34.080
Cock it again.

17:35.440 --> 17:37.080
-Cock it again.
-JOHN: Cock it again.

17:37.240 --> 17:38.440
Round two.

17:40.800 --> 17:42.320
-(GUN COCKS)
-ARTHUR: Mmm.

17:43.240 --> 17:45.480
Look at that fucking face, John boy.

17:46.480 --> 17:48.080
Look at that face.

17:49.240 --> 17:50.880
Now he feels it.

17:51.560 --> 17:53.840
But you won't feel nothing

17:54.520 --> 17:58.680
until you point that thing on a man.

18:00.720 --> 18:03.640
So do it.

18:10.720 --> 18:13.440
There you go, young boss.

18:14.880 --> 18:17.720
There you go. Now you feel it.

18:17.800 --> 18:20.040
Now you feel what we feel.

18:20.920 --> 18:23.520
This is what it's like.

18:24.520 --> 18:28.040
Michael, that's a Webley.

18:28.640 --> 18:30.160
Jumps on the hammer.

18:30.760 --> 18:32.600
How does it feel, Michael, huh?

18:33.920 --> 18:36.240
Better than having a pen
in your hand, isn't it?

18:37.080 --> 18:41.160
More like having your cock in your hand.
Yeah.

18:41.760 --> 18:43.040
Yeah, it is.

18:45.640 --> 18:47.520
One squeeze.

18:48.480 --> 18:49.480
(GRUNTS)

18:50.320 --> 18:51.320
I'm gone.

18:52.440 --> 18:54.200
I'm fucking meat.

18:54.600 --> 18:58.600
Michael, you fucking watch
that Webley don't jump. You know that?

18:58.880 --> 19:01.280
When you pull that fucking trigger,

19:02.600 --> 19:06.960
and the body of the man you shot
wraps itself around your ankles,

19:08.720 --> 19:11.640
-they pile up.
-(MICHAEL BREATHING HEAVILY)

19:12.360 --> 19:15.800
It gets to the point
where you can't walk in a room

19:17.080 --> 19:19.440
without bringing
a load of them with you.

19:24.000 --> 19:25.440
POLLY: What's going on?

19:33.680 --> 19:34.680
What's going on?

19:34.960 --> 19:39.400
Polly, we're just
educating the boss here

19:40.640 --> 19:42.400
one our side of the business.

19:44.640 --> 19:48.200
Michael, get in the house.

20:05.480 --> 20:08.360
I'm not a fucking kid any more.

20:29.760 --> 20:32.240
(GUNSHOTS)

20:40.160 --> 20:42.200
(GUNSHOTS)

21:34.960 --> 21:36.200
You've come to tell me it's cancel led.

21:36.280 --> 21:37.720
No, why would it be?

21:37.800 --> 21:38.880
I read the papers.

21:38.960 --> 21:41.400
-This is business.
-It won't work.

21:42.360 --> 21:44.480
I told your brother,
this whole fucking plan won't work.

21:44.560 --> 21:46.800
If Tommy wants to keep this secret...
Tell him.

21:46.880 --> 21:50.080
There was a woman in a fur coat
walking through here in broad daylight

21:50.160 --> 21:53.280
like the Queen of fucking Sheba
asking about armoured cars.

21:53.360 --> 21:57.040
During a period of grieving,
some things were allowed to slip.

21:57.560 --> 22:00.440
We know the woman.
We're dealing with it.

22:01.080 --> 22:04.440
Now, take a look at this list.

22:04.520 --> 22:06.320
These are all the men
who work the night shift

22:06.440 --> 22:09.120
who are members
of the South Birmingham Communist Party.

22:09.200 --> 22:12.760
You've got six weeks. Sack them all.

22:23.440 --> 22:25.000
Are you fucking mad?

22:25.880 --> 22:27.040
He is.

22:28.000 --> 22:29.000
Yeah.

22:29.320 --> 22:31.160
Every factory in the city
will come out on strike.

22:31.240 --> 22:34.520
So? You find reasons.

22:36.120 --> 22:37.480
You set them up.

22:38.800 --> 22:40.000
You sack them.

22:40.080 --> 22:41.240
